JOHANNESBURG - Leading international public relations company, Bell Pottinger has cut ties with Oakbay Investments.The British-based company, says it's ended the relationship with the Gupta-owned company, because of targeted smear campaigns.READ: Oakbay Investments CEO quitsBell Pottinger accuses the South African Communist Party (SACP) of sparking a social media campaign against it.Oakbay contracted the company last year to improve its public image in South Africa.READ: Country in deep state capture crisis: Save SAThe PR company claims direct attacks against it and its staff, has forced it to terminate the deal with immediate effect.The company insists that while working for Oakbay, it's seen no evidence of any wrong-doing.eNCA